The paper proposes a novel approach to feed-forward neural network interpretation, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed method is applied to image classification tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves partitioning the space of sequences of neuron activations, which is a technique used in neural network analysis (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of interpretable models such as logistic regression and decision trees, which is a topic in natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
